import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['delay'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay')
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('How does distance affect delay?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['time'].dt.hour, y=data['time'].dt.minute, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Hour of Day')
    ax.set_ylabel('Minutes')
    ax.set_title('What is the average time of flights?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
